t cooling efficiency, yet is prone to flooding, whereas\nthe superhydrophobic surface repels the liquid, but has poor cooling\nefficiency. The bi-phobic surfaces provide a middle path with reasonable\ncooling effectiveness and low flooding probability.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 15 Apr 2020 15:33:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 29 May 2020 15:07:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-07-15"}
