um entropy $S_Q = 10^{-122}$, $n$\ndecreases till the planck level $(n = 0)$ and enters the post-planckian phase\ne.g: $n = 1, 2,...,n_{inflation} = 10^{12},... ,n_{cmb} =\n10^{114},...,n_{reoin} = 10^{118},...,n_{today} = 10^{122}$ with the most\nclassical value $H_{today} = 10^{-61}$, $\\Lambda_{today} = 10^{-122}$,\n$S_{today} = 10^{122}$. We implement the Snyder-Yang algebra in this context\nyielding a consistent group-theory realization of quantum discrete de Sitter\nspace-time, classical-quantum gravity duality symmetry and a clarifying\nunifying picture.(Abridged)\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 15 Apr 2020 14:07:56 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 4 May 2020 01:01:10 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 21 Apr 2022 18:01:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-04-25"}
